      <!-- Tab 1 -->
      <input type="radio" name="ludhiana_tabs" class="tab ml-4" aria-label="About Ludhiana" checked="checked" />
      <div class="tab-content border-base-300 bg-base-100 p-10 space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-secondary">About Ludhiana</h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-justify text-base-content/90">
          Ludhiana, often called the <strong>Manchester of India</strong>, is the
          largest city in Punjab and a major industrial hub of northern India. Known
          for its vibrant textile industry, hosiery exports, and entrepreneurial
          spirit, Ludhiana blends tradition with progress. Beyond its economic
          prowess, the city is rich in Punjabi culture — from lively folk dances and
          sumptuous cuisine to warm hospitality. The Sutlej River runs along its
          northern edge, offering a serene contrast to the city’s bustling life.
          Whether you’re walking through old bazaars, exploring Gurudwaras, or
          enjoying a glass of lassi at a roadside dhaba, Ludhiana promises an
          experience full of heart and energy.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Tab 2 -->
      <input type="radio" name="ludhiana_tabs" class="tab" aria-label="Gallery" />
      <div class="tab-content border-base-300 bg-base-100 p-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-secondary mb-6">Gallery</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
